  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is Lazy Loading?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Lazy loading is a technique where non-critical resources are loaded only when they are needed, such as when they appear in the user's viewport."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use Lazy Loading?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Lazy loading reduces initial page load time, saves bandwidth, and improves performance, especially for pages with many images or heavy content."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<img src=\"image.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Lazy Image\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Lazy Loading Images"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Modern browsers support native lazy loading using the loading=\"lazy\" attribute."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<img src=\"photo.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Example\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Lazy Loading with JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "You can use Intersection Observer API to implement custom lazy loading."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const images = document.querySelectorAll('img');\n\nconst observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries, observer) => {\n  entries.forEach(entry => {\n    if (entry.isIntersecting) {\n      const img = entry.target;\n      img.src = img.dataset.src;\n      observer.unobserve(img);\n    }\n  });\n});\n\nimages.forEach(img => observer.observe(img));"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Lazy Loading Videos"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<video controls preload=\"none\">\n  <source src=\"video.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">\n</video>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Benefits of Lazy Loading"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Faster initial page load**",
        "**Reduced bandwidth usage**",
        "**Better user experience**",
        "**Improved SEO performance**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "When Not to Use Lazy Loading"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**For above-the-fold content**",
        "**For critical UI elements**",
        "**For important hero images**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use native lazy loading where possible**",
        "**Provide placeholder or skeleton UI**",
        "**Combine with image optimization (WebP)**",
        "**Avoid lazy loading critical resources**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Lazy loading everything including critical content**",
        "**Not providing fallback for unsupported browsers**",
        "**Using heavy JavaScript unnecessarily**",
        "**Forgetting alt attributes for images**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Lazy loading is a powerful technique to improve web performance. When used correctly, it enhances speed, reduces resource usage, and improves user experience."
    }
  ],

